    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That \"staying calm\" thing is easier said than done when they're being so sneaky about it. It's not even loud arguments, it's just these little subtle jabs and passive-aggressive \"just clarifying\" comments that make the other person look incompetent. It feels really low-level and malicious. Is there a way to address the specific nature of these small, underhanded behaviors without making it seem like I'm overreacting to minor stuff?",
