      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those subtle jabs can be particularly damaging. When addressing the issue, try framing it as a concern for the team's overall performance and morale, rather than just the specific behavior. You can say, \"I've noticed that there have been some comments made during our meetings that have created a distraction. I want to make sure we're all working together effectively, and that we're not undermining each other's work.\" This approach focuses on the impact on the team, rather than the individual behavior.",
